annotation.TEXT: Oh, and it looks like the Zelda skins have changed now. Zelda's arrows are stronger, but her sword attacks are weaker. (It says "Arrows deal more damage, sword attacks deal less damage".)
Yeah, I'm low on time again, and I doubt there are any more clocks around here.
Ooh, hidden blocks. I immediately suspected there might be some here when I saw the screen scroll further to the right than expected.
And now I have 45, which is a gain of 16. So, either I glitched an extra coin out of the block due to the way I was hitting it, or they've changed it so that you can get 16 coins instead of 15.

Wow, the wing power up wore off already? It lasted way longer when I used it with Sophia III in 3-2 (and this was still true when I replayed the levels in the new version too). Does the wing power up's duration vary depending on the character or something?
And, actually, I think I'm going to stop here for today. I took a long time on just those two levels, and I want to show off all of the skins again now, so you guys can see what the new skins are.
I'll just make my way up onto the ceiling now.
...and Lance's brighter Contra and Atari skins (which also leave out the "Bean" from his name).

Ooh, sky bonus with a checkerboard floor and chains all over the place in the background. Yep, that's totally what you'd expect to see in the sky instead of clouds. (This is a neat look for a bonus area, though.)
Oh, there's hidden blocks here, probably so I can reach the higher-up coins.
Hmm... The coins here seems to be saying something, which makes me think this room wasn't part of the original SMB Special (unless "EXPLODING RABBIT" existed back in 1986)...
The Old Man from BS Zelda and the Old Man from Link's Awakening are two of the new skins.
How many bombs do I have anyway? 20. I don't know if that's how many I had previously (before the version update), but whatever.
Oh, that's interesting. However, I've already used Samus in castles twice in this playthrough, but maybe Dark Pit could get some use out of it in another castle.
There's the vine I climbed up, so I'm done backtracking here.
Unfortunately, I guess Lakitu (Pidgit in this case) can't be frozen, but I can freeze his Spinies (Porcupos).
Now, there are five new skins for Link. I'll point them out when I get to them.
Agh! Stupid jerk!
Yep, there's Skull Man from Mega Man 4.
Ooh, there's a hidden 1-up.
Now, obviously, I'm gonna backtrack to regain power ups here.
Well, I'd go back and gorge on some of those coins, but I'm low on time again...
20 appears to be the cap on bombs anyway, so it doesn't really matter what I had before.
...Lance's Super C skin (Which says "Lance" instead of "Lance Bean")...
I think I'll go up the vine again just to get away from Pidgit for a while.
Well, now I do! I collected it kind of fast, but that was an exclusive-to-Special clock item, which adds 100 to the timer.
Roll from Mega Man 8 is new.
Aw, but they're walking off a cliff... Oh, but I can stun a Buzzy with my boomerang, which will allow me to try bombing it anyway!
SMBS sky bonus perfects: 1
Oh, man. Those elevators aren't synched very well. Maybe scrolling one of them off screen temporarily will help.
I love tearing apart bricks, in case you hadn't noticed.
It did, but now I'm low on time. Oh, and there's a warp zone in this level that I was told to check out. I'll make sure to do so.
"TIME BOMB SET! ESCAPE IMMEDIATELY!"
Cut Man from Wily Wars is new. Also, Fire Man from Mega Man 1 is new, and he comes with immunity to Fire Bars, which is neat.
I thought there was another pair of hidden blocks there. (Oh, and there might've been another pair of hidden blocks on the far left of the "EXPLODING RABBIT" coins that I missed. Oh, well.)

Oh, also, I noticed that the coins that were over that one pit in SMBS 3-1 were removed in this version. I haven't checked to see if the original SMB levels have had all of their errors fixed yet, though.
Now, Bass only gets one new skin, which you probably saw briefly there. It's Skull Man. (I will bring the cursor back down to him again.)
Ooh, Wave Beam. I forget if I showed this off earlier, but I'll leave the tutorial text on screen for several seconds here regardless.
Oh, we have a new hazard here-- an icicle, like from Ice Climber, I think. (They also exist in Mario Bros. as well.)
Ooh, a vine! Ooh, a Varia that I can actually reach this time!
This takes me to the goal, but I was also told to use a couple of hidden blocks to jump over the flagpole here.
Yes, missiles! Eat it, Pidgit! It's interesting how the first missile pickup gives you 10, and then subsequent pickups only give you 2.
Okay, so "HELLO!" is written in clouds. Umm... Hi. Oh, god... I'm just about out of time here! Hurry, hurry!
I sure have collected quite a number of missiles.
Looks like there's one new Luigi skin, with his white outfit from the original SMB (third from the left on the bottom row).
KA-BOOOOM!!!
Huh, Ice Beam. Well, I suppose I should try it out.
Okay, so I can hit the icicles with my sword/wand. Also, there's another new enemy, the Sidestepper crab from Mario Bros. (not Super Mario Bros.).
What, it gives me the bow and arrows? Oh, wait! Look at my status bar, just under my score! I just got a whole ton of stuff!
There were also votes for Endless Eight, "Slash Man (SMWC user) is back!", and to play Lost Levels on both Normal and Hard (I'll do Normal at least).
Nuts, but even if I got the perfect again, it would've been a duplicate perfect, and I wouldn't have added it to the perfect counter again.
Well, back to coin collecting.
Yes, got the Varia back again. Now, let's go back even further to the beginning of the level and see if I can get the Wave Beam again.
Oh, but there's another clock! I do like how grabbing the clock instantly changes the music accordingly if I was low on time.
I guess I could use missiles if I wanted to murder stuff.
Doesn't look like there are any new Mario skins, but I'll go over them again anyway.
Yep, there's the warp zone... to world question mark?

Alright, now if I didn't suddenly decide to stop after 4-2, I would've used Skull Man in 4-3 and Fire Man in 4-4, so that's what I'm gonna do next time. However, I'll probably do 5-1 next time as well, so you guys can vote for who I use there! To be continued...
There are three new Ryu skins: The orange Ryu Clone from Ninja Gaiden 2, Hayate from Shadow of the Ninja, and Kaede from Shadow of the Ninja.
And, unfortunately, Sophia III didn't get any new skins, but I'll move the cursor over all of them anyway.
Huh, Dark Pit? Yeah, that's one of the new skins. I'll go over them later. For now, the votes wanted me to use Samus's Super Metroid "Justin Bailey" skin, which I guess would be this one.
Oh, and there's the wing power up again. Now, Samus doesn't have a proper "swimming" form, so she'll just get increased jump height with this, which might be handy against Lakitu.
Whoa! I was trying to see if I could strike it with my magic wand, but missed. At least it didn't hit me!

Yes, this means that I won't get a time bonus or fireworks, but that's okay, and I'll be sure to turn off Infinite Time for the next level. Also, if there was stuff hidden around the "HELLO!" clouds, let me know!
I do believe that this "Exploding Rabbit" item just gave me every single upgrade that I could possibly get with this character!
Whoa, it's an "Exploding Rabbit" item!
Oh, yeah. Apparently, Super Mario Land themes are among the new music added to this version.
Also, unfortunately, it takes like twice as many shots if I want to actually kill freezable enemies now.
Now, I think there's another Special-exclusive item hidden in this level besides the wing. I'm going to try to find it.
Quint from Mega Man 2 (GB) is new.
Perfect! I think I prefer this over the Ice Beam. (However, there wouldn't happen to be anything like the Spazer or Plasma Beams in SMB Crossover, would there?)
Aha! Found it! The Lucky Star (or Rosario in this case)! It wipes out all on screen enemies when picked up! (And it even makes the Rosario sound effect here!)
I want to see if my bombs work on Buzzies...
Heck, yeah! Perfect!
And the last two new Mega Man skins are Francesca and Doropie from The Krion Conquest.

Now, unfortunately, this version update was incompatable with my previous save file, so I played through the first 3 worlds again, using the same characters, and collecting the same items, so that everyone's status should be the same as it was here before.
Wait, that's weird. I've been picking up tons of bombs all this time, and I never got this tutorial message before now (not even back when I replayed 1-1 with Ralph in this current version).

Hello, and welcome to a new version of SMB Crossover! It's just been updated to version 3.1 (well, 3.1.01 specifically), and comes with stuff such as new character skins and the Lost Levels maps, which I think I'll be doing after I finish the SMB Special maps.
Now, Mega Man gets six new skins, which I'll point out when I get to them.
SMBS demo count: 5
Man, Samus has just been having really lousy luck lately, even in my previous "and a half" episode!

Oh, and it just resets the room! Seriously? Okay, I'm going to cheat a little bit here and turn on Infinite Time so I won't die to time up, because I would've finished well in time anyway if I hadn't jumped over the flagpole, and I didn't get any items for going that way.

Alright, now up next, I believe there was a vote for Old Man, which is a Link skin. Oh, and the other alt. skin votes included SNES SMB1 Mario, Skull Man (Bass), and Fire Man (Mega Man). And those last two I believe are new skins added to this version.
Also, it might be a good idea to not accidentally hit the missile firing button and waste a missile on the underside of a solid block. (At least Samus can't harm herself with her own missiles!)
There were multiple Old Man skins there, but I've decided to go with the NES one.

Of course, I saved after each level so that I could reload that save if the RNG gave me completely different items along the way (or if I screwed up), which happened multiple times, but I eventually got everyone what they had before, I think...
Oh, it's a bonus room! But, I don't have much time for this!
Well, I guess this Old Man can kick anyone's butt now!
Oh, of course it's 4-1, so we've gotta have Lakitu.
Yeah, yeah. I'm escaping, I'm escaping. Ooh, and I got the 5000 plus 6 fireworks.
And the other three new skins are Dark Knight Cecil from FF4, Paladin Cecil from FF4, and Bartz from FF5.
Samus has three new skins: Two new variations of Dark Samus from Metroid Prime 3 (the ones on the left and right), and Dark Pit.
Now, AWESOME SPREAD GUN guy Bill gets four new skins. First, there's Bill's Super C skin...
I just noticed something while watching my footage back here. Note that I have 29 coins before I start hitting this multi-coin block.
Simon has one new skin, Soleiyu from Castlevania 2 (GB) in the lower left.
Umm... Is there anything over here? I have a feeling there is, but I don't want to waste forever searching for it.
Votes for Google to change the comments back: At least 226,034.
